    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Each time this ship-in-a-bottle is observed, something isslightly different. One time it might have three masts.Another time, the figurehead might have changed fromdragon to narwhal, or the rigging has become a light shade ofmauve. The only constants are the cannons, its malevolent 'grin', and the tentacles. This ship is, in fact, a baby mimic,that hasn't quite mastered the art of 'mimicking'.</p>\n                <p>As an action, you can uncork and upend the bottle, casting the spell <em>find familiar </em>requiring no material components. The familiar takes the statistics of the <strong>ultra-mimic offspring </strong>(see appendix B) and is friendly to you and your companions. Ifthe mimic is killed, a new mimic appears 8 hours after you fillthe bottle with water and salt.</p>",
